  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various mechanisms, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Mandating record-keeping and transaction monitoring\n\n2. Investigation Techniques\n- Forensic accounting\n- Financial tracing\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Using advanced technology and data analysis\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Extradition agreements\n\n4. Prosecution Strategies\n- Targeting financial intermediaries\n- Seizing assets\n- Criminal charges for money laundering\n- Substantial financial penalties\n\n5. Regulatory Frameworks\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) guidelines\n- Compliance requirements for financial institutions\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and investigative strategies.",
